attribute escape "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
================================================================

NAME
----

attribute escape - **This function is deprecated as of WordPress 2.8.0. Please use

SYNOPSIS
--------

**This function is deprecated as of WordPress 2.8.0. Please use
[esc\_attr](/Function_Reference/esc_attr "Function Reference/esc attr")
instead.**

This function escapes or encodes HTML special characters (including
single and double quotes) for use in HTML attributes. It works like the
standard PHP `htmlspecialchars` except that it doesn't double-encode
HTML entities (i.e. `&amp;` will remain unchanged, rather than encoded
to `&amp;amp;`).

`attribute_escape` can be found in `/wp-includes/formatting.php`.

USAGE
-----

` <?php echo attribute_escape($text); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

`$text`
:   (*string*) Text to be escaped.

